Mozilla Public License 2.0 notice and be placed under `src/firefox-derived/`.

Task #4 fixes the Firefox-derived source boundary to:

- Upstream repository: https://github.com/mozilla-firefox/firefox
- Upstream commit: e28b34ab33dbf49364999070168cbb7e11e8e5bd
- Upstream source path:
  `browser/components/screenshots/overlayHelpers.mjs`
- Local derived files:
  `src/firefox-derived/overlay-helpers.ts`,
  `src/firefox-derived/region.ts`, and
  `src/firefox-derived/window-dimensions.ts`

The local files listed above are the approved TypeScript adaptation targets for
Chrome MV3 visible-viewport selection helpers. Firefox privileged APIs, closed
shadow root access, cross-origin iframe traversal, full-page capture, and
scroll stitching are not part of this adaptation.

Task #5 Stage 6 adds Firefox Screenshots UI asset adaptations:

- Upstream repository: https://github.com/mozilla-firefox/firefox
- Upstream source paths:
  `browser/components/screenshots/ScreenshotsOverlayChild.sys.mjs`,
  `browser/components/screenshots/content/menu-visible.svg`, and
  `browser/components/screenshots/content/menu-fullpage.svg`
- Local derived file:
  `src/firefox-derived/screenshots-ui-assets.ts`

The local UI asset file adapts the Firefox Screenshots preview face SVG and
menu icons for Chrome MV3 Shadow DOM rendering. Firefox product branding,
privileged APIs, localization ids, telemetry, and full-page capture behavior
are not part of this adaptation.

